iled summary of research on attachment, highlighting the work of Mary Ainsworth, Mary Main, Allan Sroufe, and Peter Fonagy. The second portion focuses on clinical applications with children, adolescents, and adults. Brief vignettes and lengthier case illustrations consider a verity of attachment disorders and treatment approaches, paying special attention to clinical method and technique, process dimensions, and transference and countertransference phenomena. Cases are set in a range of treatment venues, such as college and family counseling service, community mental health centers, and private practice, and involve an ethnoculturally and clinically diverse clientele.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAttachement chez l'enfantxÉtudes transculturelles. 0aAttachement chez l'enfant. 0aAttachment behavior in childrenvCross-cultural studies. 0aAttachment behavior in childrenxCross-cultural studies. 0aAttachment behavior in children. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Services.2bisacsh1 aRingel, Shoshana, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247240uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/bran1339040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231508551423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231508551/original  a978-3-11-044247-2  Columbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK